summary: An ordinance amending section 1 of Ordinance No. 29288, entitled: "An ordinance setting aside and transferring the control and jurisdiction of the Board of Park Commissioners that certain tract of land described as follows to-wit: that triangular block owned by the City of Seattle, situated in what is known as Terry's 2nd Addition to the City of Seattle, bounded on the east, by Broadway on the Northwest by Terrace Street and on the Southwest by Terry Avenue, for park purposes", approved April 24, 1912.
